      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 108: 🟡 Suggestion: The `CountDownLatch` is a single-use object initialized at field declaration time, but `bootstrapDaemon()` can be invoked multiple times throughout the app lifecycle (e.g., reconnect scenarios). After the first bootstrap (success or failure), the latch is permanently at zero and will never gate subsequent bootstrap attempts. If the daemon is ever restarted after a crash, `ensureDaemonStarted()` will return immediately without waiting for the new bootstrap to complete.\n\nConsider using a resettable synchronization mechanism (e.g., a `Mutex` + `Condition`, or an `AtomicReference\u003cCompletableFuture\u003cBoolean\u003e\u003e` that is replaced on each bootstrap attempt).",
      "revId": "129c962b78a28478b65da379649e37004db31b34",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
