      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 196: 🔴 Critical: `CountDownLatch` is a one-shot primitive — once counted down it can never be reset. If `bootstrapDaemon()` throws an exception, the latch is still counted down (line 181). Any subsequent call to `ensureDaemonStarted()` will have `await()` return `true` immediately, even though the daemon never actually started. The method will report success when the daemon is broken.\n\nConsider replacing `CountDownLatch` with a `CompletableFuture\u003cBoolean\u003e` or a simple `@Volatile var` + `Object.wait()/notifyAll()` that records the actual start result, so callers can distinguish success from failure. Alternatively, check `daemon.isStarted` after the await:\n\n```suggestion\n            daemonStartedLatch.await(25, TimeUnit.SECONDS) \u0026\u0026 daemon.isStarted\n```",
      "revId": "129c962b78a28478b65da379649e37004db31b34",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
