      "message": "Line 207: 🟡 Suggestion: On Android 14+ (API 34), `onTimeout()` is the system\u0027s signal that a short-lived foreground service has exceeded its allowed duration. Simply returning without calling `stopForeground()`/`stopSelf()` does not guarantee the service stays alive — the system may force-stop it anyway, and ignoring the callback could lead to undefined behavior or future compatibility issues.\n\nIf active calls need longer foreground time, consider transitioning to a different foreground service type (e.g., `FOREGROUND_SERVICE_TYPE_PHONE_CALL`) when a call begins, rather than ignoring the timeout.",
      "revId": "129c962b78a28478b65da379649e37004db31b34",
