      "message": "[critical] Line 74: 🔴 Critical: `ensureDaemonStarted()` blocks for up to 25 seconds. This method is called from `JamiPushService.onMessage()`, which runs on the main thread (Service lifecycle callback). Blocking the main thread for more than 5 seconds triggers an ANR.\n\nThis should be moved to a background thread, similar to how the Firebase variant uses `serviceScope.launch(Dispatchers.Default) { ... }`. For example:\n\n```suggestion\n    fun onMessage(remoteMessage: Map\u003cString, String\u003e) {\n        // Move to background thread to avoid ANR — ensureDaemonStarted blocks\n        Thread {\n            if (!ensureDaemonStarted()) {\n                Log.e(TAG, \"onMessage: daemon failed to start within timeout, push may be lost\")\n            }\n            mAccountService.pushNotificationReceived(\"\", remoteMessage)\n            mNotificationService.processPush()\n        }.start()\n    }\n```",
